HEADWORD: Gaylussite
<hw>Gay"lus*site`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Named after
<etsep>Gay-Lussac</etsep>, the French chemist.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A yellowish white, translucent mineral, consisting of the
carbonates of lime and soda, with water.</def>⟦br⟧
